<a href="/questions/1401716-why-do-all-the-three-boys-think-the-others">why do all the three boys think the others are better with girls? I can believe that they are all a bit insecure, but how come none of them can see it in the others and somehow they are each others&#39; object of envy regarding &#39;girl skills&#39;? Will they discuss it and have a good laugh about it in the last book, or what is the deal with it?</a>
